3) Program counting vowels in command-line arguments
class Test {    public static void main(String[] args) {        int count = 0;        for(String s : args) {            s = s.toLowerCase();            for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++) {                char ch = s.charAt(i);                if(ch=='a'||ch=='e'||ch=='i'||ch=='o'||ch=='u') {                    count++;                }            }        }        System.out.println("Vowels = " + count);    }}

Execution
java Test Java Hello

Output
Vowels = 4

